I"À'<h3 id="project-description">Project Description</h3>

<p>In this project, my partner and I built both the hardware and software for a social robot inspired by Pixar Animation Studioâ€™s Luxo Jr.. For the base robot arm, we used the open-source mini 6-DOF manipulator platform that we developed (for Master of Engineering project). The end-effector, which contains both the lamp and a Raspberry Pi camera, was custom designed and manufactured for this project. To achieve organic behavior, we implemented face-detection and tracking algorithms on the Raspberry Pi 3B+. In addition, we implemented teach and replay algorithms to train the robot arm for movement routines, in order to quickly and easily achieve sophisticated motion. Overall we were successful and created a robot that is lively and interacts with humans in its surroundings, powered by a resource-restricted embedded device.</p>

